solution:
As power $\mathrm{P}=F . v .=\frac{F \ell}{t}$
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \text { or, } v\left(M \frac{v}{t}\right)=\frac{F . \ell}{t} \\
& \Rightarrow \quad M v^2=F \ell \ell \\
& \Rightarrow \quad F=\frac{M}{\ell} v^2=m v^2 \\
& {\left[\because \frac{M}{\ell}=m(\text { given })\right]}
\end{aligned}
$$

Acceleration produced in upward direction
$$
\begin{aligned}
& \mathrm{a}=\frac{\mathrm{F}}{\mathrm{M}_1+\mathrm{M}_2+\text { Mass of metal rod }} \\
& =\frac{480}{20+12+8}=12 \mathrm{~ms}^{-2}
\end{aligned}
$$
Tension at the mid point
$$
\begin{aligned}
\mathrm{T} & =\left(\mathrm{M}_2+\frac{\text { Mass of rod }}{2}\right) \mathrm{a} \\
& =(12+4) \times 12=192 \mathrm{~N}
\end{aligned}
$$
